            <infoLink name="Bolt Pistol" id="a713-7b4a-7e45-0d3a" hidden="false" type="profile" targetId="e9ac-c779-51bb-3c9a"/>
            <infoLink name="Independent Character" id="9960-09a3-2d56-8a62" hidden="false" type="rule" targetId="4a60-7f7e-c37f-a4d6"/>
          </infoLinks>
          <rules>
            <rule name="Rending" id="7e79-c42a-7245-ca42" hidden="false">
              <description>Tyranids with rending claws inflict a wound automatically and ignore armour saves on to-hit rolls of 6. Other successful hits must roll ot wound as normal. If the creature rolls a 6 for Armour Penetration they then can roll an additional dice to determine the total Armour Penetration value.</description>
            </rule>
            <rule name="Legion Overseer" id="bac4-cfeb-a3f5-05be" hidden="false">
              <description>If Carnac is included in a Tyrant&apos;s Legion army list, then a single Legion Retaliator Squad may be chosen as a Troops Choice (they still select a Veteran Skill as if they were an elite choice).</description>
            </rule>
            <rule name="Arch-Centurion" id="626d-18a0-d435-b9c8" hidden="false">
              <description>Carnac benefits from the Stubborn special rule as outlaid in the Astral Claws Special Rules, but it does not confer to any Auxilia units that he is leading. If an Auxilia unit within 12&quot; of Carnac fails a Morale Check from shooting casualties or losing a combat remove D3 models as per shooting casualties as Carnac makes a bloody example of the shirkers. The unit is then assumed to have passed the Morale test after all and continues to fight on.</description>
            </rule>
          </rules>
        </selectionEntry>
      </selectionEntries>
      <costs>
        <cost name="pts" typeId="4ed5-2f92-9abc-2870" value="100"/>
      </costs>
    </selectionEntry>
