      </infoLinks>
      <rules>
        <rule name="Operate Behind Enemy Lines" id="54e7-5e86-68ed-d116" hidden="false">
          <description>Instead of being set up normally, one unit of Veteran Scouts can be sent our ahead of the army to operate behind enemy lines. If you decide to use this option, the Scout unit must be kept in reserve even in scenarios that don&apos;t normally allow reserves to be used. When the Scouts arrive from reserves, they must enter play from the table edge that the opposing side&apos;s reserves enter from or retreat towards. If the opponent does not have a table edge then roll randomly to see which edge they enter from.</description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
    </selectionEntry>
