      <rules>
        <rule name="Old &amp; Wise" id="9646-4340-0033-f953" hidden="false">
          <description>If a Sons of Medusa army includes a Venerable Forge-Lord it may re-roll the dice if the mission being played has a dice roll to see who gets the first turn.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Hard to Kill" id="9c1f-f242-52db-adff" hidden="false">
          <description>When a Venerable Dreadnought takes a glancing or penetrating hit, you may force your opponent to re-roll the resulting damage. You must accept the result of the second roll, even if it is worse.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Auto-Repair Simulacra" id="888c-846d-f5f5-55ca" hidden="false">
          <description>If the Forge-Lord is destroyed on either a Glancing Hit result of a 6, or a Penetrating Hit result of a 4, roll an additional dice. On a 6, the Forge-Lord is not destroyed as only a redundant system was damaged by the blow and counts as Crew Shaken instead.</description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
    </selectionEntry>
    <selectionEntry type="unit" import="true" name="Iron Thane Vaylund Cal" hidden="false" id="9aad-1b01-38fb-9597">
