          <rules>
            <rule name="Targetting Priority" id="b887-98ab-8d1f-3386" hidden="false">
              <description>A heavy bolter/assault cannon Sentry gun will fire at the nearest non-vehicle unit it can hit. A lascannon/multi-melta Sentry gun will fire at the closest enemy vehicle or monstrous creature it can hit. If no preferred target can be hit they will shoot at non-preferred targets.</description>
            </rule>
            <rule name="Damage" id="0e97-9857-1e7c-2296" hidden="false">
              <description>A Sentry Gun is destroyed by any glancing or penetrating hit.</description>
            </rule>
            <rule name="Firing Modes" id="2a02-b679-6a05-b170" hidden="false">
              <description>At deployment, you must select a firing mode. It cannot be changed once the game begins.

Point Defence Mode: Choose a fixed 90 degree arc. The gun will engage enemy targets up to 24&quot; away within the arc.

Sentry Mode: The gun will fire at the nearest enemy target within 12&quot; that it can see.</description>
            </rule>
          </rules>
        </selectionEntry>
