  <categoryEntries>
    <categoryEntry name="The Tyrant&apos;s Legion" id="be91-12d4-9193-7b29" hidden="false">
      <rules>
        <rule name="The Tyrant&apos;s Due" id="312e-b2a0-ec6c-c04d" hidden="false">
          <description>As cannon fodder for the Astral Claws, any Astral Claws&apos; Infantry or Biker unit may claim +1 to any cover saves granted because of fire passing through any Auxilia infantry unit to reach them (a 4+ becoming a 3+ for example). However, if this bonus is claimed the Auxilia suffers D3 wounds per unit firing through them against which this save bonus has been claimed. Wounds inflicted this way are distributed as per wounds for normal shooting attacks and have no AP value.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Second Line Units" id="f23e-f956-3693-e8c6" hidden="false">
          <description>Any Chimera, Leman Russ, Leman Russ Demolisher or Basilisk may be &quot;downgraded&quot; to Second Line status. If done, the vehicle costs 10 points less than usual, but at the beginning of the control player&apos;s movement phase, it must roll a D6 and apply the result:
1: Break Down: The vehicle&apos;s engine has given out and counts as having suffered an immobilized result. Do not roll again for the rest of the battle.
2: Gear Box Issues: The vehicle may only move 6&quot; in its next movement phase.
3-5: Running fine...for now: Vehicle moves as normal.
6: Frontline Unit: The vehicle moves as normal. Do not roll again for the rest of the battle.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Defensive Force" id="af6d-665f-5097-f822" hidden="false">
          <description>The Tyrant&apos;s Legion may include an extra Heavy Support selection in exchange for two Fast Attack selections. </description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
    </categoryEntry>
  </categoryEntries>
</catalogue>
